        "translator": "",
        "content": "Bhante Henepola Gunaratana (or “Bhante G” as his students call him) is a Sri Lankan monk born in 1927 who has lived and taught in the United States since 1968. He is the founder of Bhavana Society, a donation-based monastery and retreat center in West Virginia, and is the author of the highly acclaimed meditation manual, Mindfulness in Plain English.",
